latestIgtvVideos.caption:
Reposted from @seenstories 

From wanting to lose weight to please a boy back in high school to starving myself after being body shamed for not being skinny enough when I was modelling a few years after, I’ve made a lot of mistakes. 

But the good thing about making mistakes is that you can learn from them.

The reason behind my transparency about having struggled with eating disorder and embracing recovery is because I kept it a secret for so long, I let my mind control me, which made it worse.

I thought I was the only one battling this but only after being vocal about my struggle have I realised how rampant this struggle is.

Being honest and sharing my lows on social media has made me stronger, more committed to recovery and has helped me redefine who I want to be, unapologetically.

I am still recovering and it is probably the hardest thing I’ve ever worked towards. But it is a work in progress and I will continue to try every single day, every single meal and every single bite until I reach a point of absolute food freedom. 💛

I would like to thank @seenstories for featuring my story! And @antra_mudgal for being one of the most patient journalists I’ve worked with! 

 I hope this reaches someone who needs to hear it. 🤍

If you want to share your story, DM me or @defeating.disorders. Let’s destigmatise the conversation around eating disorders, mental health and body shaming together!

Thank you @BBC for having me speak about my eating disorder recovery journey. 

It was such an honour to be one of the panelists alongside @nimratofficial @dikshamalik.malik and @nehaparulkar. 

I didn’t think I would breakdown while sharing my story but I hope I can reach anyone who needs to hear this and prevent someone from falling a prey to the toxicity of this never-ending ED cycle.

Living with an eating disorder, isn't living. It's just existing.

Last year I decided to finally let go and commit to recovery because I didn’t want to exist meaninglessly. I wanted to regain my life and my happiness. 

But in all honesty, I didn't make 100% progress over night. 

Like the pursuit of any goal, this one also came with its own fair share of ups and downs. There were days when I wasn't just weak, I actually wanted to be…

Days I didn't just miss my eating disorder, I craved it. 

Days I didn't just dislike my body, I loathed it…

But I persevered. I stayed strong and consistent. I went for therapy and learnt more about the importance of nutrition. I spoke words of love and affirmation to my changing body and thanked it for doing all that it does for me. 

So just in case someone needed to hear this today... 

Self-love starts with self-acceptance. Unless we practice kindness towards ourselves, happiness will always be a destination, not a journey. 

I'd also like to end by reminding  us that no one should grieve or suffer in silence. Let's share our struggles and be more receptive to those of others. 🤍

Send a message to me or my NGO @defeating.disorders if you want to share your story. 

Let’s destigmatise mental health. Let’s diversify the narrative. Let’s talk about what we don’t talk about.

✨2024 mantra ✨

I have been repeating this in front of the mirror since last year and it has CHANGED my life. 🤍

I know who I am
I LOVE who I am
I like what I do
And I like HOW I do it…
And I like my mistakes
And I like the way I learn
And I like the PACE
With which I learn my mistakes.
I don’t want to be anybody else,
BUT ME!!! 🥹🥰🫶🏼

Original audio is from an interview with @zoesaldana 🤍

#mantra2024 #selflove #happinessisachoice #confidence #affirmations #soulfamily #spiritualtok #spiritualtiktok #woketok #believeitachieveit #affirm #lightworker #claimit #111

This trend has my heart 🥺

Today is World Mental Health Day. And if you’ve ever struggled, just know that it will get better and you don’t have to go through it alone.

I’m posting this reel to reflect on so many emotions I’ve felt in the past couple years that impacted my mental health. But for better or for worse, if I could go back in time… I wouldn’t change a thing. 

All the mistakes, failures and losses have shaped me into the girl I always wanted to be. 

If you’re still reading this, I want to say thank you. You have added something to my life. I go to sleep every night with a smile on my face. Thank you for being here, for writing to me, for trusting me and sharing your stories with me, for letting me talk, eat, dance, sing, cry and just letting me live my purpose. 🥺 I am so grateful for you. 

If you’re STILL reading… I hope this reel becomes a gentle reminder that every experience, every person and every conversation teaches us something. And even though it may not always seem like it, if you’re hurting right now or if you feel like it will never get better - I promise you, it will. And it will make you stronger and much more resilient. 

You’ll become a force to reckon with, you’ll attract only good people, you’ll laugh more and LOUDER! 🤭 

Just give time, some time… ⏱🤍 You’ll look back and see how every moment was a piece integral to complete the giant puzzle called “Life”. ☺️💛

Life is good when you’re with family 🥹❤️

My sister and I, along with our partners, took our parents on a 10-day trip around Europe, and honestly, it was one of the most special things we’ve ever done together. 

Being in new places, away from the usual routine, gave us the chance to really slow down and just enjoy each other’s company. We laughed so much, had the best food, shared quiet little moments, and made memories I know we’ll hold close forever. 

It just felt really beautiful to be together like that and time flew by so fast. 

This is your sign to take your parents on a trip! They don’t love anything more than spending time with their kids 🥹❤️

This is YOUR sign to make the girls trip out of the group chat 💅🤩💬

Here’s a quick summary:

1. Start planning the trip 6 months in advance. 

2. Pick a destination that works for everyone. It should be safe, easy to get to and FUN for a girls trip! 

3. Where you stay is SO important. 

Keep it central in the city, so you can walk around, make sure everyone has a comfortable and safe experience :)

If you’re going to Prague, check out PragueDays.com because I couldn’t recommend them enough! ✨
